entries.meaning: (obsolete) The character or nature of a goodly person; goodliness.
(archaic, poetic) Goodly appearance or looks; beauty.
examples: The lilies, of great goodlihead, divinely tall, sway with a stately, languid grace; the Canterbury bells are all ringing.
